title: [Western Waterway, Charl's Teeth]
description: As a result of the widening channel to the south, the water calms relative to the fury of its energy farther north.  Puffins, their beaks bright orange against their black and white feathers, nest on the ragged ledges of the Teeth's boulders, fast asleep.
paths: Obvious paths: north, northeast, east, southeast, southwest
